** Solution **
Create Key Pair via AWS Management Console:

1- Log into the providing crendentials.
2- Ensure the region at the top right is set to N. Virginia (us-east-1).
3- Search for EC2 service and open it:
  a- In the left sidebar, scroll down to “Network & Security” → “Key Pairs”.
  b- Click “Create key pair”.
  c- Fill the form:
        Name: "given name"
        Key pair type: RSA
        Choose the Private key file format:
            .pem (to use SSH directly)
            or
            .ppk (to use PuTTY)
   d- Click “Create key pair”.
      The private key file will download automatically. Save it securely.
